text: eligible patients were men and women aged 18–55 years with rrms (as defined by the revised 2005 macdonald criteria15) and an expanded disability status scale (edss) score of 0–5.5, with at least one of the following characteristics: ≥1 documented relapse(s) within the 12 months before screening; ≥2 documented relapses within the 24 months before screening or at least one t1-weighted gadolinium-enhanced (gd+) lesion detected on brain mri at screening.
